  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much do psychologists charge for a cognitive behavioural therapy?",
  "response": "The cost of cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT) can vary widely depending on several factors, including the psychologist's location, experience, and whether the therapy is provided in a private practice or through a public health service. Here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. **Private Practice:**\n   - In the United States, the average cost per session can range from $100 to $250.\n   - In the UK, private sessions may cost between \u00a350 and \u00a3150 per session.\n   - In Australia, private sessions might range from AUD $150 to AUD $250 per session.\n\n2. **Public Health Services or Community Clinics:**\n   - Costs can be significantly lower or even free, depending on the country's healthcare system and whether the psychologist is covered by insurance or public health plans.\n\n3. **Insurance Coverage:**\n   - If you have health insurance, check if it covers mental health services, including CBT. Some plans cover a portion of the cost, while others may cover it entirely, subject to copayments or deductibles.\n\n4. **Sliding Scale Fees:**\n   - Some psychologists offer sliding scale fees based on your income, which can make therapy more affordable.\n\n5. **Online Therapy Platforms:**\n   - Platforms like BetterHelp or Talkspace may offer more affordable options, with sessions ranging from $60 to $90 per week, depending on the subscription plan.\n\nTo get an accurate estimate, it's best to contact psychologists directly in your area and inquire about their specific rates and any potential discounts or payment plans they might offer.",
